page.title: 09INSH MARSHES - 2
page.content:
The Reserve is of international importance as a wintering spot for the{Whooper swan. }The list of species would seem endless but in short, many types of{ducks, rails, buzzards, {black-headed gulls, redpolls}and {spotted flycatchers}all breed here. Less common visitors include {peregrines, merlins and grass-hopper {warblers. Golden eagles}can be spotted soaring above the Monadhliath mountains.
Mammals are plentiful too. {Roe deer are frequently seen as are{rabbits}and {brown hares. Badgers}and{foxes}are harder to spot. In winter{red deer and{blue hares}come visiting. This is well known as one of the best otter habitats in the area.
